fields.name: Absolutely Fabulous
fields.preparation: Mix the Vodka and Cranberry juice together in a shaker and strain into a glass. Top up with Champagne.

fields.name: Death in the Afternoon
fields.preparation: Easy as you like, pour the absinthe into a chilled glass, top with champagne. Must be drunk mid afternoon for the optimum effect.

fields.name: Amaretto Shake
fields.preparation: Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend at high speed until smooth. Serve in chilled glass garnished with bittersweet chocolate shavings.

fields.name: Arizona Antifreeze
fields.preparation: Pour all ingredients into shot glass and slam !!!!

fields.name: Karsk
fields.preparation: Put a copper coin in a coffe-cup and fill up with coffee until you no longer see the coin, then add alcohol until you see the coin. Norwegian speciality.

fields.name: Gin Fizz
fields.preparation: Shake all ingredients with ice cubes, except soda water. Pour into glass. Top with soda water.
fill glass with crushed ice. Add vodka. Add a splash of grand-marnier. Fill with o.j.

fields.name: Lazy Coconut Paloma
fields.preparation: Mix the coconut liqueur (preferably tequila) with the grapefruit juice and top with soda water. Garnish with a large grapefruit slice against the inside of the glass.

fields.name: Irish Russian
fields.preparation: Add the ingredients in the order listed in the recipe. Care must be taken when adding the Guinness to prevent an excess of foam. Do Not add ice.

fields.name: Figgy Thyme
fields.preparation: In a lewis bag, crush up some ice like a baller/maniac (@glacioice). Pour your precious ice into a collins glass. In a cocktail shaker, muddle the figs and thyme together. Add honey vodka, lemon juice, and a large ice cube (@glacioice). Shake until well chilled, and strain into glass. Add tonic water and finally 2 dashes of angostura bitters. Garnish with sliced figs and thyme.

fields.name: Derby
fields.preparation: Pour all ingredients into a mixing glass with ice. Stir. Strain into a cocktail glass. Garnish with a sprig of fresh mint in the drink.

fields.name: Kool First Aid
fields.preparation: Add Kool Aid to a double shot glass, and top with rum. Slam and shoot.

fields.name: Gin Sour
fields.preparation: In a shaker half-filled with ice cubes, combine the gin, lemon juice, and sugar. Shake well. Strain into a sour glass and garnish with the orange slice and the cherry.

fields.name: Snakebite and Black
fields.preparation: Put blackcurrant squash in first up to about 1cm in glass. Then add the larger and cider one after another.

fields.name: Fruit Flip-Flop
fields.preparation: Place all ingredients in the blender jar - cover and whiz on medium speed until well blended. Pour in one tall, 2 medium or 3 small glasses and drink up.

fields.name: Amaretto Sunrise
fields.preparation: Mix together the amaretto and orange juice. Pour into glass and then add the grenadine untill you see the sunrise.

fields.name: Stinger
fields.preparation: Pour in a mixing glass with ice, stir and strain into a cocktail glass. May also be served on rocks in a rocks glass.

fields.name: Absolut limousine
fields.preparation: Fill Absolut into a glass. Add Lime juice. Add Ice and lime wedges.

fields.name: Egg-Nog - Classic Cooked
fields.preparation: In large saucepan, beat together eggs, sugar and salt, if desired. Stir in 2 cups of the milk. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick enough to coat a metal spoon and reaches 160 degrees F. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining 2 cups milk and vanilla. Cover and regfigerate until thoroughly chilled, several hours or overnight. Just before serving, pour into bowl or pitcher. Garnish or add stir-ins, if desired. Choose 1 or several of: Chocolate curls, cinnamon sticks, extracts of flavorings, flavored brandy or liqueur, fruit juice or nectar, ground nutmeg, maraschino cherries, orange slices, peppermint sticks or candy canes, plain brandy, run or whiskey, sherbet or ice-cream, whipping cream, whipped. Serve immediately.

fields.name: Tequila Surprise
fields.preparation: Fill shot glass with Tequila. Add drops of Tobasco sauce.

fields.name: Aloha Fruit punch
fields.preparation: Add 1/4 cup water to ginger root. Boil 3 minutes. Strain. Add the liquid to the guava, lemon and pineapple juices. Make a syrup of sugar and remaining water. Cool. Combine with juices and pineapple. Chill throroughly.

fields.name: Black & Tan
fields.preparation: Fill pint glass half full with Bass. Next pour Guiness over a spoon slowly until glass is full. If done correctly the Guiness will stay on top and the Bass on bottom hence the name Black & Tan.

fields.name: Negroni
fields.preparation: Stir into glass over ice, garnish and serve.

fields.name: Bijou
fields.preparation: Stir in mixing glass with ice and strain

fields.name: Bora Bora
fields.preparation: Prepare in a blender or shaker, serve in a highball glass on the rocks. Garnish with 1 slice of pineapple and one cherry.

fields.name: Raspberry Cooler
fields.preparation: Pour the raspberry vodka and soda into a highball glass almost filled with ice cubes. Stir well.

fields.name: Kool-Aid Slammer
fields.preparation: Fill half the shot glass with the kool-aid first. Then put a paper towel over the top of the glass and slowly pour in the vodka. If you do it right, you should be able to see that the two liquids are separated, with the vodka on top. Now slam it! The last thing you'll taste is the kool-aid.

fields.name: Bee's Knees
fields.preparation:
Shake ingredients with crushed ice
Garnish with orange peel

fields.name: Tia-Maria
fields.preparation: Boil water, sugar and coffe for 10 mins and let cool. Add rum and vanilla. Put in clean bottle(s) and leave for 1 week before using.

fields.name: Holloween Punch
fields.preparation: Take a bunch of grape juice and a bunch of fizzy stuff (club soda, ginger ale, lemonlime, whatever). Mix them in a punch bowl. Take orange sherbet and lime sherbet. Scoop out scoops and float them in the punch, let them melt a little so that a nasty film spreads all over the top of the punch but there are still "bubbles" in it in the form of sherbet scoops. Looks horrible, tastes just fine.

fields.name: Bermuda Highball
fields.preparation: Pour brandy, gin, and dry vermouth into a highball glass over ice cubes. Fill with carbonated water and stir. Add the twist of lemon and serve. (Ginger ale may be substituted for carbonated water, if preferred.)

fields.name: New York Lemonade
fields.preparation: Serve in a chilled cocktail glass. Lemon and sugar the rim. Stir and Strain.

fields.name: Lady Love Fizz
fields.preparation: Shake all ingredients (except carbonated water) with ice and strain into a cocktail glass over two ice cubes. Fill with carbonated water, stir, and serve.

fields.name: Gluehwein
fields.preparation: Boil sugar and spices in water, leave in the water for 30 minutes. Strain the spiced water and mix with the wine. Heat slowly until short of boiling temperature. (To remove alcohol, let it boil for a while.) You may add lemon or orange juice to taste. Serve in irish coffee cup.

fields.name: Caribbean Orange Liqueur
fields.preparation: Pare very thinly the bright-colored rind from the oranges (no white). Blot the peel on paper towels to remove any excess oil. Put peel in a 4 cup screw-top jar. Add 2 cups vodka. Close jar. Store in a cool, dark place for 2 days or until the vodka has absorbed the flavor. Remove peel and add remaining vodka. Close jar and add remaining cup of vodka. Close the jar and store in a cool dark place at least 1 month to age.

fields.name: Egg Nog - Healthy
fields.preparation: Whip egg substitute and sugar together, combine with the two kinds of milk, vanilla, and rum. Mix well. Chill over night. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Makes 6 servings.

fields.name: 151 Florida Bushwacker
fields.preparation: Combine all ingredients. Blend until smooth. Garnish with chocolate shavings if desired.

fields.name: Alice in Wonderland
fields.preparation: Just mix the three ingredients one to one to one

fields.name: Pink Gin
fields.preparation: Pour the bitters into a wine glass. Swirl the glass to coat the inside with the bitters, shake out the excess. Pour the gin into the glass. Do not add ice.

fields.name: Salty Dog
fields.preparation: Pour all ingredients over ice cubes in a highball glass. Stir well and serve. (Vodka may be substituted for gin, if preferred.)

fields.name: Sweet Bananas
fields.preparation: Place all ingredients in the blender jar - cover and whiz on medium speed until well blended. Pour in one tall, 2 medium or 3 small glasses and drink up.

fields.name: Chocolate Drink
fields.preparation: Melt the bar in a small amount of boiling water. Add milk. Cook over low heat, whipping gently (with a whisk, i would assume) until heated well. Don't let it boil! Serve in coffee mug.

fields.name: The Philosopher
fields.preparation: Add all the spirits in a shaker (best to use Hendricks gin) as well as the orange bitters and lemon juice. Strain into a Margarita glass, top with Prosecco.

fields.name: Balmoral
fields.preparation: In a mixing glass half-filled with ice cubes, combine all of the ingredients. Stir well. Strain into a cocktail glass.

fields.name: Sherry Eggnog
fields.preparation: Shake sherry, powdered sugar, and egg with ice and strain into a collins glass. Fill with milk and stir. Sprinkle nutmeg on top and serve.

fields.name: Broadside
fields.preparation: Half fill the glass with ice cubes. Crush the wormwood and add to ice. Pour rum, scotch and butters, then serve!

fields.name: Black Forest Shake
fields.preparation: In a blender put ice cubes, chocolate syrup, cherry brandy, vodka, and milk. Blend very well.

fields.name: A Splash of Nash
fields.preparation: Drop shot glass with banana & melon liquers into a 9 oz hi- ball glass containing soda water and cranberry juice. Drink in one shot.

fields.name: Zombie
fields.preparation:
Blend at high speed for no more than 5 seconds.

Pour into a glass, add ice cubes to fill, then add the garnish.

*Donnâ€™s mix: Bring 3 crushed cinnamon sticks, 1 cup of sugar and 1 cup of water to a boil, stirring until the sugar is dissolved.

Simmer for 2 minutes, then remove from the heat and let sit for at least 2 hours before straining into a clean glass bottle.

Then add 1 part of the syrup and 2 parts of fresh grapefruit juice together.

fields.name: Brandy Alexander
fields.preparation: Shake all ingredients (except nutmeg) with ice and strain contents into a cocktail glass. Sprinkle nutmeg on top and serve.

fields.name: Coffee Liqueur
fields.preparation: Combine coffee, sugar and water. Simmer 1 hour and let cool. Add vanilla and vodka. Age in sealed jar 2 to 3 weeks.

fields.name: Cream Soda
fields.preparation: Pour 1oz of Spiced Rum into a highball glass with ice. Fill with Ginger Ale.

fields.name: Alice Cocktail
fields.preparation: Shake well, strain into a large cocktail glass.

fields.name: Jewel Of The Nile
fields.preparation: In a mixing glass half-filled with ice cubes, combine all of the ingredients. Stir well. Strain into a cocktail glass.

fields.name: GG
fields.preparation: Pour the Galliano liqueur over ice. Fill the remainder of the glass with ginger ale and thats all there is to it. You now have a your very own GG.

fields.name: Absinthe #2
fields.preparation: Mix together and let sit a few days. Strain through a coffee filter. To serve mix 1 part absinthe to 4 parts water, add ice, enjoy.

fields.name: Surf City Lifesaver
fields.preparation: Lots of ice and soda top up in tall glass with cherry and a grin.
